      "comment": "KERRY'S CADILLAC (2) copped a check in the run last time and never threatened when sixth (18.29) in a Other at this track. Safe beginner and drawn well close to the inside. Has the ability and expected to go close. ROUGH GIRL MEL (4) was quickly into stride and burnt early from out wide where she gave a sight, finishing third (17.77) and beaten 1.75 lengths over 305m at this track. Will give a great sight again. LAP TO BURN (8) has mixed form a little and missed the frame the last two but was a Other winner three back (17.73) at this track over 305m. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from on outside draw. Rates a winning chance on best. LADY BOMBSHELL (1) cannot be left out over a shorter distance.",
